  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#### Call Me Maybe Remix\r\nGrace noticed that the vocals for Call Me Maybe by Carly Rae Jepsen build in energy and lead to a big beat drop, an expressive, high-energy moment in the song, that would be fun to exaggerate even further. \r\n\r\n> The song already has a fun beat drop so I wanted to make it even bigger by adding more sound layers to create an even better dance track. \r\n\r\nGrace is using **abstraction** by focusing on accentuating one part of the song instead of the whole thing. \r\n\r\n**Your task:** Use abstraction to organize your code into loops that build to the beat drop with rich, layered sounds. Your song should use at least 10 unique tracks, but focus only on the ones that best support the mood and pacing of the vocals. Use the example for inspiration!",
    "offer_browser_tts": "true",
    "use_secondary_finish_button": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
